          <title>Olivia Hussey, star of the 1968 film 'Romeo and Juliet,' dies at 73</title>
          <description><![CDATA[LONDON (AP) — Olivia Hussey, the actor who starred as a teenage Juliet in the 1968 film “Romeo and Juliet,” has died, her family said on social media Saturday. She was 73. Hussey died on Friday, “peacefully at home surrounded by her loved ones,” a statement posted to her Instagram account said.]]></description>
